<item>
            <title>[LU-6910] Configurable values for OST reserved size</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6910</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;osp_pre_status=-ENOSPC is used to skip OST from object allocation. The error was set when OST available space is less than 0.1% of total OST size. This value is not configurable. For many cases 0.1% is too low, because append works for existing files. So, procfs files was added for configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
